1. useradd

Creates a new user account in the system.

useradd krishna
2. passwd

Sets or updates the password for a user.

passwd krishna
3. exit

Terminates the current shell session or logs out the user.

exit
4. su

Switches to another user account (default: root if no username).

su krishna
5. cat /etc/passwd

Displays all user account details stored in the system.

cat /etc/passwd
6. cat /etc/group

Displays all group information in the system.

cat /etc/group
7. userdel

Deletes an existing user account.

userdel krishna
8. useradd -m (and note on -a)

-m creates a home directory for the user; -a is not valid with useradd.

useradd -m krishna
9. gpasswd -a and -M

-a adds a user to a group; -M sets (overwrites) group members.

gpasswd -a krishna devteam
gpasswd -M krishna,ram devteam
